<b>Posted On:</b> 6:29 a.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Realmweavers' Editorial:<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=281" TARGET=_self>Realmweavers' Editorial:</A> (Kiwi)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Many of you haven't had a chance to play the game, and with this NDA, I am going to be as non-descriptive as possible.

<BR>Realmweaver, Have you actuallyplayed the game? If so, have you adventured in a party? Well, in a party you tend to
<BR>take on certain responsibilities, and one of them is to protect your party members as best as you can. Well, lets say
<BR>your PK-ing idea goes into effect and I am venturing with you. We are running through whereever and a monster
<BR>jumps out of who know where and starts hitting you from behind. You race to type to your fellow party member you
<BR>are being attacked and as you are I notice you are being hit for a good deal of damage. I spin around, hit the key to
<BR>target that monster and hit the key to start attacking. Oops, my target accidentally targeted you, and with no safety
<BR>measures I knock you down more hit points, maybe even killing you (ya know mages just don't seem to have that
<BR>much health to them). I killed you, and I didn't mean to do it. You may say this wont happen, but if I had a free month
<BR>of EQ release play for every time I tried to target a monster only to find I am targeting a PC...jeez, I could play free for
<BR>life. This is just one scenario where if we could hit each other the system would fail us at times. I'm sure someone
<BR>else out there has another.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
